A j ≤ Bi + sti + ti j + ldep(p)(1− x p i j) ∀i, j ∈ P∪D p ∈ M (10)
A j ≤ B p i + sti + ti j + ldep(p)(1− x p i j) ∀i ∈ DEP, j ∈ P p ∈ M (11) Apj ≤ Bi + sti + ti j + ldep(p)(1− x p i j) ∀i ∈ D, j ∈ DEP p ∈ M (12)
Constraints (7)–(12) state that the arrival time at node j must be equal to Bi+sti+ ti j (to B p i +sti+ ti j) if xpi j = 1 and i /∈ DEP (and i ∈ DEP). More precisely, the constraints impose that, if x p i j = 1, A j can not be bigger than Bi + sti + ti j or B p i + sti + ti j, depending if i /∈ DEP or not, respectively. In the constraints, ldep(p) is the end of the time window at the depot of vehicle p.
