Initially, coefficients α , β , γ and τ are set to given values α0, β0, γ0 and τ0, respectively, and each time a new incumbent solution is found are modified by a factor of 1+δ . In the VNS, δ is randomly chosen between 0.05 and 0.1, and changes every time a new incumbent solution is found.
